{"type":"hook.start","data":{"hookInvocationId":"cca92ada-cbf4-4fc8-b096-457df20f8c5a","hookType":"postToolUse","input":{"sessionId":"a61f4d8b-7d71-4d8c-b58c-9df9517b5266","timestamp":1777077884720,"cwd":"/tmp/sv-e23a4caccbac4d34b33258326e12d35a","toolName":"view","toolArgs":{"path":"/tmp/sv-e23a4caccbac4d34b33258326e12d35a/developer-report.md"},"toolResult":{"resultType":"success","textResultForLlm":"1. ## Developer Complaint\n2. \n3. Our developers report that running `dotnet build` from the terminal feels sluggish\n4. for incremental builds. Even when nothing has changed, CLI builds take 2-4 seconds,\n5. while the same project rebuilds nearly instantly inside Visual Studio.\n6. \n7. We've already verified:\n8. - No analyzers are slowing things down\n9. - Incremental build targets are working (targets do skip correctly)\n10. - The project itself compiles in <500ms\n11. \n12. The overhead seems to come from MSBuild process startup and re-evaluation of the\n13. project graph on every CLI invocation.\n14. \n15. We're looking for ways to speed up the developer inner loop when building from the\n16. command line, especially for quick edit-build-test cycles.\n17. ","toolTelemetry":{"properties":{"command":"view","options":"{\"truncateBasedOn\":\"tokenCount\",\"truncateStyle\":\"middle\"}","inputs":"[\"path\",\"command\"]","resolvedPathAgainstCwd":"false","fileExtension":"[\".md\"]","viewType":"file"},"metrics":{"resultLength":757,"resultForLlmLength":757,"responseTokenLimit":42000},"restrictedProperties":{}},"sessionLog":"\ndiff --git a/tmp/sv-e23a4caccbac4d34b33258326e12d35a/developer-report.md b/tmp/sv-e23a4caccbac4d34b33258326e12d35a/developer-report.md\nindex 0000000..0000000 100644\n--- a/tmp/sv-e23a4caccbac4d34b33258326e12d35a/developer-report.md\n+++ b/tmp/sv-e23a4caccbac4d34b33258326e12d35a/developer-report.md\n@@ -1,17 +1,17 @@\n ## Developer Complaint\n \n Our developers report that running `dotnet build` from the terminal feels sluggish\n for incremental builds. Even when nothing has changed, CLI builds take 2-4 seconds,\n while the same project rebuilds nearly instantly inside Visual Studio.\n \n We've already verified:\n - No analyzers are slowing things down\n - Incremental build targets are working (targets do skip correctly)\n - The project itself compiles in <500ms\n \n The overhead seems to come from MSBuild process startup and re-evaluation of the\n project graph on every CLI invocation.\n \n We're looking for ways to speed up the developer inner loop when building from the\n command line, especially for quick edit-build-test cycles.\n \n","skipLargeOutputProcessing":true}}},"id":"3c3f1ed1-2e22-486d-8c75-2528b1e774ac","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:44:44.720Z","parentId":"16c2c934-7f88-431b-bc11-c89ef487fde3"}
